benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: Successful updates with required parameters only (TC01), with payAllUnpaidInvoices (TC02), with pluginProperty (TC03), with all optional headers (TC04), and the no-unpaid-invoices case (TC05).
Authorization and header validation: Tests cover 401 unauthorized (TC12) and missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header (TC11).
Input validation: Tests cover invalid accountId format (TC06), invalid paymentMethodId format (TC07), and invalid/malformed UUID edge cases (TC23).
Non-existent resources and cross-account checks: Tests cover non-existent account (TC08), non-existent paymentMethod (TC09), and paymentMethod not belonging to the account (TC10).
Error handling and service availability: 503 service unavailable (TC13) and related 400/404 responses for various invalid inputs.
Edge and boundary cases: tests for extra query parameters (TC14), maximum pluginProperty entries (TC15), min/max UUIDs (TC16), empty pluginProperty array (TC24).
Audit/logging: coverage for audit-related details in TC04 and regression checks in TC20.
Concurrency and performance: concurrency across multiple methods (TC22), heavy unpaid invoices (TC17), slow downstream dependency (TC18).
Regression tests: regression scenarios TC20 and TC21.
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit test to verify PUT semantics disallowing payload-based partial updates (the endpoint uses setDefault via path/queries).
Concurrency on the same resource: dedicated test for two clients updating the same account simultaneously.
Caching Behavior: no tests for HTTP caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
Rate Limiting: no tests for rate limiting or throttling.
recommendations: Add explicit race-condition test for same-resource updates to verify proper locking or last-write-wins behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify burst handling and proper error codes if limit exceeded.
Add caching header tests if static responses are cached or to validate ETag/Cache-Control behavior.
Add a Partial Update test to guard against invalid payloads for PUT if semantics evolve.
